# {{n-g|Forms the partitive article.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Il mange '''du''' pain.|He eats bread. / He eats '''some''' bread.}}

====Usage notes====
* The partitive article is used with [[uncountable]] nouns instead of the indefinite article (which is only used with countable nouns). English and most other European languages do not use any article in such cases.
* Like the indefinite article, the partitive article becomes simple {{m|fr|de}} with grammatical objects in negated sentences: {{m|fr||Il ne mange pas '''de''' pain.|He doesn't eat bread.}}
* After the actual preposition {{m|fr||de|t=of, from}}, the partitive article is deleted. So one can never say {{m|fr||*de du}} or {{m|fr||*de de la}}.
